&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About the Role&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a&amp;nbsp;Platform Engineer&amp;nbsp;to join our Platform Infrastructure team supporting Cumberland and FICCO&#39;s trading operations. In this role, you&#39;ll be the&amp;nbsp;driving force behind how we deploy, observe, and scale our systems - making deployments faster, system health more visible, and infrastructure more self-service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your&amp;nbsp;focus will be on automating deployment patterns, building observability that&amp;nbsp;actually surfaces signal over noise, and evolving our platforms to meet the demands of&amp;nbsp;mission-critical trading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be for our Chicago office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Converge and improve application deployment patterns across containerized and non-containerized workloads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build self-service infrastructure provisioning using Terraform/Terragrunt and Ansible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive CI/CD excellence and advocate for modern software delivery practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance monitoring and alerting to enable proactive capacity management and early failure detection - without the noise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and implement technologies that improve container orchestration, workload management, and system visibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn and support in-house tools for infrastructure management and deployment workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in on-call rotation to resolve trade-critical issues and identify opportunities for automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain system security through regular patching, reporting, and compliance with security standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Challenge the status quo and advocate for meaningful change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Tech&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting mission-critical, high-performance trading systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Kubernetes experience (deployment, troubleshooting, optimization)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Prometheus and Grafana for monitoring and observability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid Python skills for automation and tooling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with Ansible and Terraform/Terragrunt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Linux systems knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of CI/CD pipelines and software delivery best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with TLS and network protocols (including multicast and WebSockets)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AWS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Intangibles&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You learn quickly and genuinely enjoy exploring new technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You take ownership - problems don&#39;t sit idle on your watch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate clearly, both in writing and conversation, especially across distributed teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You stay composed under pressure and manage competing priorities effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can accommodate occasional off-hours calls and escalations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
